social_posts.post_text: For me these are the top two monitors. I played around with getting them both set up and where they both sound the best. Integrating two sets of monitors is tough but the reward is incredible. Two completely different lenses to see the full picture.
Massive thanks to @mark.duane.morton for helping me find this 1969 Les Paul Custom. This thing sounds incredible. I can’t even put into words how stoked I am!!!

Words can’t even describe how excited I am to release this. Slipknot has always been one of my favorite bands, and I remember when Jay joined. My best friend Spencer and I were completely blown away by how well his style fit the band. We saw them live with him and he was incredible. Surreal to get to work with him and engineer/mix his drums! Here it is. Mixwave - Jay Weinberg!!! An immense amount of work went into this. I hope you love it!!!
The apogee pultec is my favorite because it doesn’t smear and blur the sound of the entire mix. Most of the other plugins mess with the source sound too much!

I’m back on the desk!!! Massive shout out to @sondhus. If you want a desk that’s minimalistic and has minimal reflections the Arvo is it! I took a sine sweep measurement with and without the desk and there was no difference. Insanely stoked on this and I feel more comfortable at my workstation!

Mixwave Milkman is out!!! This amp is the clean machine! It can do sooo many sounds that I feel no other plugins are doing right now! Insanely musical. Also try the pop top discrete op amp pedal on your kick/snare/bass/vocals/drum bus/entire mix bus! It’s incredible. 🎛🌊🥛
The amp rack is back! These cover every color of the SOUND spectrum for me. What’s your favorite?

Literally the BEST amp ever made. This is my number one. I play on it everyday and the way it reacts with pedals is absolutely insane. I’ve re-tubed it with all NOS RCA tubes. Short bottle 6l6’s and various grey plates that I shot out in the preamp sections. It’s crazy how different all tubes sound. Even the same models. My favorite drive pedal as well! I loveeee playing guitar again!

I am very proud to announce my brand new plugin in collaboration with @mixwave .  Introducing MixWave: Spiritbox - Mike Stringer.  We’ve been working on this for almost two years now, and I can honestly say it’s the most fun and inspiring plug-in I’ve ever used.  It caters to every sound I’d want out of a plug-in, and I am finding myself having endless creativity while using it.  The wide variety of tones, effects, and possibility this plugin gives you is really something special, and I can’t wait for you to try it out yourself.  Massive thank you to @taylorlarson , and the entire team at MixWave for knocking this out of the park.  I hope you enjoy!
Has anyone tried these? Absolutely MASSIVE! @coil_audio

Thank you MixWave for bringing this sample library into the world. I’m proud to be involved in something so elaborately constructed on a technical side, and also something so delicately curated on a personal side. I cherish every bit of detail that was made possible by the very sweet and generous team at MixWave. I hope you enjoy the end product as much as I enjoyed the journey that led here! Mixwave: Turnstile - Daniel Fang out now.

YES… I had to mic this entire kit. 🫠
1962 ebony block Les Paul. First time ever playing PAF’s and now I understand the hype. Nothing modern that I’ve tried sounds close at all. What a sick guitar! #gibsunday
Not bad for being on hiatus for the last 3 years!!! 🤣

So incredibly stoked to introduce MixWave’s first MIXING plugin! The Coil Audio CA-70s. Making mixing plugins was the entire reason we started this company and the day has finally come. This is a very unique tool and we feel like nobody has pulled off this sound and feel in the digital world. It sounds MASSIVE! It makes digital sound sources come alive and sound analog by adding tremendous weight and depth. It’s been all over our mixes for months. We hope you love it as much as we do!
Got to record/mix this for New Years. Was super fun! Thanks for having me! ♥️
